# <%= current_page.data.title %>

The WebOps Community of Practice is our longest running COP and exists to coordinate the DevOps, Pipeline and Infrastructure practices across the department. This is important as we work with embedded WebOps in teams, so require a space to share knowledge and build standards. This helps facilitate our "hub and spoke" approach where one team can solve a problem then template it out for others to benefit from.

## Membership

Meetings of the community are every Monday at 2pm in the #opg-webops-community channel. All members of the OPG WebOps profession and interested parties (Technical Architects, Heads of Profession, Developers, Product Managers, people from other departments and so on) are welcome.

